properties.headline: Flood Watch issued February 4 at 4:07PM EST until February 6 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Jackson KY
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Jackson has issued a

* Flood Watch for portions of south central Kentucky and
southeast Kentucky, including the following areas, in south
central Kentucky, Laurel, McCreary, Pulaski, Rockcastle,
Wayne, and Whitley. In southeast Kentucky, Bell, Clay, Harlan,
Jackson, Knox, Leslie, Letcher, Owsley, and Perry.

* From Wednesday evening at 7 p.m. through Thursday morning at 7
a.m. EST.

* Multiple rounds of moderate to at times heavy rain will continue
to fall across portions of southeastern Kentucky. More
widespread heavier bands of rainfall will be possible Wednesday
evening and night, continuing into Thursday, as a storm system
approaches eastern Kentucky. This additional heavy rainfall, on
top of saturated soils, will likely lead to at least isolated
flooding issues.

* Minor flooding of low lying areas as well as rivers, creeks,
and streams will be possible.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Watch means there is a potential for flooding based on
current forecasts.

You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible
Flood Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be
prepared to take action should flooding develop.

NWSheadline: FLOOD WATCH IN EFFECT FROM WEDNESDAY EVENING THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING
